    "created_at": "2013-09-28T01:05:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-09-28T01:05:47Z",
    "body": "@brson: I'm not sure if it would be feasible, but in theory we can register handlers with `pthread_atfork` to re-initialize a fresh runtime in a new process. I don't think it's very important, so it might be too difficult to be worth the trouble.\n\nThe old system for handling daemons was for the end of the first child to signal that initialization was done, but this has been superseded by socket activation in `systemd`, `upstart` and `launchd`.\n",
