    "created_at": "2014-08-19T01:57:49Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-19T01:57:49Z",
    "body": "I think the option of using `#![no_std]` with libcore is fine. Rust does need to provide an I/O and concurrency library at a lower level than the full blown runtime, but I think that's inevitable.\n",
